{"key":"processedPost-10109288","value":{"id":10109288,"first":10108901,"last":10109509,"when":1238940870,"utime":"04/05/09 05:14 PM","content":"Tests have shown that anything over about 2% Mg will impede fruiting performance.&nbsp; Look for calcium carbonate or hydrated lime, and make sure it has low Mg percentage.&nbsp; Avoid any lime with the word 'dolomite' associated with it.&nbsp; Unless you're growing agaricus button mushrooms, a casing layer is not required with bulk substrates.&nbsp; If you can't find the correct lime, I'd suggest growing on uncased manure or straw, etc.<br />RR","title":"Re: will it work?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}